[{"location":"aog.html#AlgebraOfGraphics-Helpers","page":"AoG","title":"AlgebraOfGraphics Helpers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"aog.html","page":"AoG","title":"AoG","text":"Several convenience functions that provide simple calls to common functionality.","category":"page"},{"location":"aog.html#FigureHelpers.set_default_AoGTheme!","page":"AoG","title":"FigureHelpers.set_default_AoGTheme!","text":"set_default_AoGTheme!(;makie_config=MakieConfig())\n\nSetting sensible defaults with taking care of pt_per_unit in MakieConfig.\n\nWhen saving png, there is a difference in size between the produced figure  in print and display on a monitor and its dpi settings. This routine adjusts several seetings given in inch by deviding makie_config.pt_per_unit.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"aog.html#FigureHelpers.draw_with_legend!","page":"AoG","title":"FigureHelpers.draw_with_legend!","text":"draw_with_legend!(fig, plt; fig_pos_legend = fig[1,2], kwargs...)\n\nDraw aog plot into Makie figure, fig[1,1], and legend into subfigure.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"makie.html#Makie-Helpers","page":"Makie","title":"Makie Helpers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"makie.html#Unit-conversions","page":"Makie","title":"Unit conversions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"makie.html","page":"Makie","title":"Makie","text":"Many graphical properties are given in pixel or inches. Working with figures for international journals, however, usually requires thinking and specification in metric units.  The following function help to convert.","category":"page"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.cm2inch","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.cm2inch","text":"cm2inch(x)\ncm2inch(x1, x2, x...)\n\nConvert length in cm to inch units: 1 inch = 2.54   The single argument returns a value, the multiple argument version a Tuple. Similar to more verbose syntax using Unitful.jl: uconvert(u\"inch\",x * u\"cm\").val.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"makie.html","page":"Makie","title":"Makie","text":"Figures often look well, if the ratio between length and hight corresponds to the Golden ratio.  So we provide it here.","category":"page"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.golden_ratio","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.golden_ratio","text":"golden_ratio â‰ˆ 1.618\n\nTwo quantities are in the golden ratio if their ratio is the same as  the ratio of their sum to the larger of the two quantities.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"makie.html#Makie-Layout-switching-and-Figure-generation","page":"Makie","title":"Makie Layout switching and Figure generation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"makie.html","page":"Makie","title":"Makie","text":"Generating the same plot for paper and for a presentation, requires adjusting properties such as figure sizes, fontsizes, and graphics format. The following class helps to collect them and provide them to functions below","category":"page"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.MakieConfig","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.MakieConfig","text":"MakieConfig\n\nA collection of figure properties to tailor the same figure either for presentation in a paper or a presentation.\n\nppt_MakieConfig(;\n    target = :presentation, \n    filetype = \"png\", \n    fontsize=18, \n    size_inches = (5.0,5.0/golden_ratio), \n    kwargs...) \n\npaper_MakieConfig(;\n    size_inches = cm2inch.((8.3,8.3/golden_ratio)), \n    kwargs...)\n\nProperties and defaults\n\npt_per_unit = 0.75\nfiletype = \"png\"\nfontsize = 9   (point units)\nsize_inches = cm2inch.((17.5,17.5/golden_ratio)) (witdth x height)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"makie.html#creating-figures-with-adjusted-sizes-and-font-sizes","page":"Makie","title":"creating figures with adjusted sizes and font-sizes","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.figure_conf","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.figure_conf","text":"figure_conf(; makie_config)\nfigure_conf(width2height, xfac=1.0; makie_config)\n\nfigure_conf(size_inches = cm2inch.((8.3,8.3/golden_ratio)); fontsize=9, pt_per_unit = 0.75)\n\nCreates a figure with specified resolution/size and fontsize  for given figure size. \n\nThe first two constructors apply the settings from the config, with the possibility to adjust the width/height ration (e.g. to golden_ratio) or multiply the default x-width.\n\nThe last constructor sets the properties without referring to a config. It uses by default pt_per_unit=0.75 to conform to png display and save.  Remember to devide fontsize and other sizes specified elsewhere by this factor. See also cm2inch and save.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.figure_conf_axis","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.figure_conf_axis","text":"figure_conf_axis(...; makie_config, kwrags...)\n\nCall figure_conf but return a tuple (figure, axis). The keyword arguments are passed to the Axis(; kwrawgs...) call.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"makie.html#saving-figures-to-correct-format-and-dpi-resolution","page":"Makie","title":"saving figures to correct format and dpi-resolution","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.save_with_config","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.save_with_config","text":"save_with_config(filename, fig; makie_config = MakieConfig(), args...)\n\nSave figure with file updated extension cfg.filetype to subdirectory cfg.filetype of given path of filename. Sets pt_per_unit to makie_config.pt_per_unit.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"makie.html#Shortcuts","page":"Makie","title":"Shortcuts","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.hidexdecoration!","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.hidexdecoration!","text":"hidexdecoration!(ax;, label, ticklabels, ticks, grid, minorgrid, minorticks; kwargs...)\nhideydecoration!(ax;, label, ticklabels, ticks, grid, minorgrid, minorticks; kwargs...)\n\nVersions of hidexdecorations! and hideydecorations! with defaults reversed. This allows to selectively hide single decorations, e.g. only the label.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.axis_contents","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.axis_contents","text":"Extract axis object from given figure position. Works recursively until an  Axis-object is returned\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"makie.html#Tailored-plots","page":"Makie","title":"Tailored plots","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"makie.html#FigureHelpers.density_params","page":"Makie","title":"FigureHelpers.density_params","text":"density_params(chns, pars=names(chns, :parameters); \n    makie_config::MakieConfig=MakieConfig(), \n    fig = figure_conf(cm2inch.((8.3,8.3/1.618)); makie_config), \n    column = 1, xlims=nothing, \n    labels=nothing, colors = nothing, ylabels = nothing, normalize = false, \n    kwargs_axis = repeat([()],length(pars)), \n    prange = (0.025, 0.975), # do not extend x-scale to outliers\n    kwargs...\n)\n\nPlot density from MCMCChains.value with facets for each parameter.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FigureHelpers.jl","page":"Home","title":"FigureHelpers.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html#FigureHelpers","page":"Home","title":"FigureHelpers","text":"Concepts in Julia that have not found its proper package.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"See all the github repository.","category":"page"}]
